re":1},{"id":"recEoYRAyVeAancS0","type":"place","group":"mentioned","label":"Syria","slug":"syria_1122","score":1}],"links":[{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"rec410yOewjNfbeE3","label":"part of"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"rec0BAacWSGBXZ0zI","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"rec1ZMFtfbEvoGC73","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"recjNRR60PAuFtjha","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"rec4QEZboAvgaMvkX","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"rec4QeGbvAwa56yBh","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"recbO7tUz8fk12ExW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"recYsXWjhw6FUqHLY","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"recfrXyxhuYOczKTm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"recVYcDguYN6bVqxy","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"recc5WQixfPBowmwE","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"rec5S2a0FVulB61s7","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgaZgmvFdgwgfzp","target":"recEoYRAyVeAancS0","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recMuoqjvb7j9PfYD","ref":"2Chr.1.1","text":"And Solomon the son of David was strengthened in his kingdom, and the LORD his God was with him, and magnified him exceedingly.","year":-1015},{"id":"recrXdYguZxd5bibR","ref":"2Chr.1.2","text":"Then Solomon spake unto all Israel, to the captains of thousands and of hundreds, and to the judges, and to every governor in all Israel, the chief of the fathers.","year":-1015},{"id":"recCv8kGDPzcrBaRb","ref":"2Chr.1.3","text":"So Solomon, and all the congregation with him, went to the high place that was at Gibeon; for there was the tabernacle of the congregation of God, which Moses the servant of the LORD had made in the wilderness.","year":-1015},{"id":"recJf9visS4stoR6S","ref":"2Chr.1.4","text":"But the ark of God had David brought up from Kirjathjearim to the place which David had prepared for it: for he had pitched a tent for it at Jerusalem.","year":-1015},{"id":"rec1gfQufAt1z8TMu","ref":"2Chr.1.5","text":"Moreover the brasen altar, that Bezaleel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, had made, he put before the tabernacle of the LORD: and Solomon and the congregation sought unto it.","year":-1015},{"id":"recG9DRjNgYI299SV","ref":"2Chr.1.6","text":"And Solomon went up thither to the brasen altar before the LORD, which was at the tabernacle of the congregation, and offered a thousand burnt offerings upon it.","year":-1015},{"id":"recsxvHfH64ohqRaF","ref":"2Chr.1.7","text":"In that night did God appear unto Solomon, and said unto him, Ask what I shall give thee.","year":-1015},{"id":"recbOhlCfpEwrXKN6","ref":"2Chr.1.8","text":"And Solomon said unto God, Thou hast shewed great mercy unto David my father, and hast made me to reign in his stead.","year":-1015}]}
